<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100503227730018></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100503227730018><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6951&mid=100503227730018>A question on morality...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6951&mid=100503227730018#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 6th 2:37 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>K, here's the story.<br>Last night I was in North Ro during the event.  It was about 5am RL time (In my time zone anyway) and there were only around 17 people in zone when the snake popped.  Now, obviously a group formed almost instantly to kill it, and I was right over by the fishing huts watching the whole time.  I'm a 35 Cleric, and I was ooc'ing if I could join the group.  There was only one other cleric in zone, and as I recall, he or she was the ONLY anonomyous person there, besides myself.  There were no other wisdom casters that I saw, and certainly none in the snake group.  I believe it consisted of at least one, possibly 2 bards, a wizzie, a necro, and possibly a mage.  <br>Anyway, they dropped the snake, and people were gathering around it as one would expect.  While all the group members checked the corpse, someone said in ooc to NOT loot the snake, as the drops were being rolled on by the party members.  Again, I /who'ed the zone, myself and the other cleric were the only other anonymous peeps, and no other wis casters.<br>I managed to stick my nose in the corpse after a few minutes.  It had this Idol, and some SK shoulders, don't remember the name.  <br>So...I looted the Idol, and left.  Shortly after someone asked what happened to the SK shoulders, and it was stated by someone in the kill group that they rotted.  THIS angered me, as there was a 22 SK who I had been standing next to while the snake group dropped him, and everyone was told not to loot the corpse.<br>My question is this:  Was my looting of the Idol wrong?  As I said, there were NO wis casters in the zone either time I checked, other than myself and the other anon Cleric, and he or she was NOT in the kill group.  So, was it wrong of me to loot this Idol, when obviously if there HAD been a wis caster in the kill group they would have taken it right away?  And what of the shoulder item that rotted, forever WASTED because someone told us all not to loot the things that were not usable by the kill group?  Most of these event items have been for either one specific class, wis casters, or int casters.  It wouldn't have taken that long to decide who got what.  Since there were 3 int casters in the kill group, that's about the only thing (If an int caster item dropped) that would have needed to been rolled on.  Everything else would have been self-explanatory as to who got what.<br>Anyway, just wanting to know people's input on this matter.  Seeing that the shoulders rotted infuriated me...and knowing that the Idol would have most likely done the same makes me feel like I didn't really do anything wrong.  Just wondering here, please do not flame, just give an opinion...<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
